{"questionId":"21989","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A farmer owns a field in the shape of a triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>ABC</mtext></math> such that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AB</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>650</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>AC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>1005</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>BC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>1225</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/6bb236e9e545a23bfe955bd1634c0b1c658e250b.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The local town is planning to build a highway that will intersect the borders of the field at&nbsp;points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>E</mtext></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>DC</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>210</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>CÊD</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>°</mo></math>, as shown in the diagram below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/b837e2382d85600a860a8368eaafdde6468e25b3.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>DE</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>use of sine rule &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em>&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mtext>DE</mtext><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>31</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9980</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>210</mn><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>100</mn><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>